4. Data types - JSON supports specific data types including string, number, object, array, true, false, and null. All values must conform to these types.

6. Trailing commas - There should be no trailing commas after the last key-value pair in an object or an array.

7. Syntax errors - Any other syntax errors that violate the JSON format.
